cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, q-bio.QM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with processing and analyzing high-resolution mammalian neural images using deep learning-based methods. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel end-to-end deep learning-based method for generating compact representations of in situ hybridization (ISH) images. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep learning-based methods for analyzing gene expression data and learning functional representations of genes. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses deep convolutional denoising autoencoders (CDAE) for processing raw pixel inputs and generating compact image representations. 
5. q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods): The paper deals with analyzing gene expression data and learning functional representations of genes, which falls under the domain of quantitative methods in biology.
